f=Cybersecurity/keyring/custom/privileged-access-management/SKILL.md · in=tighter discipline accounts damage admin, root, cloud-org-owner, database-superuser, break-glass. Privileged access minimized, just-in-time (granted task removed), monitored, never standing-by-default. keys kingdom, kingdom's blast radius they get their rules. · p=Standing admin access single phished credential becomes full compromise. PAM shrinks privileged attack surface: fewer privileged accounts, granted needed, long needed, use watched stolen credential usually privileged, privileged action always visible. · wu=Any admin/root/superuser/org-owner access involved., "Who admin," "grant break-glass," "why standing admin.", Privileged-access review (stricter cadence normal reviews). · st:/ Protocol=MINIMIZE (fewest possible privileged accounts; shared admin logins; personal accountability) JUST-IN-TIME (privilege granted specific task time window, automatically removed zero standing privilege possible; operator/PAM-tool executes) BREAK-GLASS (emergency high-privilege access pre-defined, heavily logged, alerts use, reviewed after use always-on backdoor) MONITOR (every privileged action logged and, ideally, session-recorded; feeds cortex detection) REVIEW (privileged entitlements recertified short cadence; access-reviews, stricter) keyring designs; operator/PAM-tool executes; break-glass use alerts cortex. · in=**Minimize personalize.** privileged accounts work requires, tied person (no shared `admin`/`root` logins shared privilege destroys accountability). privileged account exists "just case" attack surface. **Just-in-time over standing.** goal zero standing privilege: privilege requested task, granted window, auto-revoked. Standing admin exception needs justification, default. **Break-glass defined, logged, alerted, reviewed.** Emergency access exists (you'll need it) it's pre-approved, heavily-monitored path fires alert use reviewed single time never quiet always-on super-account. **Every privileged action visible.** Logged session-recorded possible; logs prime cortex detection sources (privileged action outside granted window alert). **Stricter, shorter reviews.** Privileged entitlements recertified often normal access; blast radius justifies overhead. **keyring designs; operator/PAM executes; break-glass alerts cortex.** inversion holds even especially here, because privileged execution security agent ultimate concentration risk. · of=`## Privileged Access: [account/entitlement] \· Minimized: [personal, not shared ✓] \· Model: [just-in-time window / standing (justified?)] \· Break-glass: [defined \· logged \· alerts-on-use \· post-review] (if applicable) \· Monitoring: [logged/session-recorded → cortex] \· Review cadence: [short] \· Designed by keyring \· executed by operator/PAM` · pr=**Minimize personalize** fewest privileged accounts, shared admin., **Just-in-time over standing** zero standing privilege goal., **Break-glass defined, alerted, post-reviewed** quiet backdoor., **Every privileged action visible** prime cortex detection source., **Stricter, shorter reviews** blast radius justifies it., **keyring designs; operator executes** inversion, hardest here. · f=PAM tooling manual just-in-time (grant, task, prompt revoke) tightly-held, logged break-glass procedure, labeled manual; discipline holds without product., Legacy system requires standing admin minimize, monitor heavily, log time-boxed exception compensating control (warden). · b:with Other Skills=**identity-lifecycle access-reviews** (siblings): privileged accounts get stricter JML shorter reviews., **secrets-governance** (sibling): privileged credentials sensitive secrets., **cortex**: privileged-action logs break-glass alerts prime detection inputs., **relay/quinn (Eng/AI&Agents)**: AGENT privilege Rail relay's grants; keyring's PAM humans parallel, overlapping., **warden**: standing-privilege exceptions PAM gaps register risks.